ArrayList in Java Collections

ArrayList is a class in the Java Collections Framework that implements the List interface. It is used to store a dynamic array of elements.

Features of ArrayList
✅ Dynamic size (grows and shrinks automatically)
✅ Maintains insertion order
✅ Allows duplicate elements
✅ Allows null values
✅ Fast random access using index
❌ Slow for frequent insertion/deletion in the middle


Syntax

import java.util.ArrayList;

ArrayList<DataType> list = new ArrayList<>();